sss is a simple slideshow system that let's you:

 * drop photos from your favourite file manager
 * reorder them
 * set between-images and transition times
 * run the slideshow using gliv
 * load/save slideshow settings (list of files and times)
 * export the slideshow to a folder (copies the photos and
   creates a BASH script that runs the slideshow using gliv)

It depends on Python 2.6, PyQt4, gliv, BASH, the filemanager
to be FreeDestkop compatible. For thumbnails it uses ones
stored in .thumbnails directory (but not generates them).

How to install & use it (on Ubuntu):
------------------------------------

sudo aptitude install python-qt4 gliv
git clone git://github.com/gabrys/sss.git
cd sss
sudo cp sss /usr/bin
sss

